texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: Urchin sometimes takes it upon itself to do some weird things, and this is one of those times. If Urchin has archived a month of data, and then you ask Urchin to parse a log that contains accesses from that archived month, you'll receive this ugly error:
texts.text: Urchin sometimes takes it upon itself to do some weird things, and this is one of those times. If Urchin has archived a month of data, and then you ask Urchin to parse a log that contains accesses from that archived month, you'll receive this ugly error:

texts.label: code
texts.orig: Unable to open database for writing since it has been archived
texts.text: Unable to open database for writing since it has been archived

texts.label: paragraph
texts.orig: To fix it, cd into /usr/local/urchin/data/reports/[profile name]/ and unzip the YYYYMM-archive.zip files, then move the zip files out of the way. Make sure that the unzipped files are owned by the Urchin user and group. You should then be able to re-run your stats without a problem.
texts.text: To fix it, cd into /usr/local/urchin/data/reports/[profile name]/ and unzip the YYYYMM-archive.zip files, then move the zip files out of the way. Make sure that the unzipped files are owned by the Urchin user and group. You should then be able to re-run your stats without a problem.
